Great — it makes sense to clean this up for clarity and scalability. Your variables fall into a few categories:

Project/package metadata (PN, TN, URIs)

Download-related (DLDIR, PKGDLDIR, PKGDLFILE)

Extraction-related (EXTDIR, PKGEXTDIR, PKGDLROOT)

Paths for source/include/output (PKGDIR_SRC, LIBDIR, etc.)

Final build artifacts (PKGLIB, PKGEXE, PKGTST, etc.)

Here's a refactored and clearer naming scheme suggestion:

🧩 Package Identity
PKG_NAME := 07_zip
TGT_NAME := 07_zip
🌐 Download Info
PKG_URI     := https://github.com/cgware/cbase/archive/refs/heads/main.zip
PKG_DLFILE  := main.zip
PKG_DLROOT  := cbase-main/
📁 Directory Roots
DIR_DL      := $(PROJDIR)tmp/dl/
DIR_EXT     := $(PROJDIR)tmp/ext/
DIR_OUT     := $(PROJDIR)bin/$(ARCH)-$(CONFIG)/
📁 Package-Specific Directories
DIR_PKG         := $(PROJDIR)$($(PKG_NAME).DIR)
DIR_PKG_SRC     := $(DIR_PKG)src/
DIR_PKG_INC     := $(DIR_PKG)include/
DIR_PKG_DRV     := $(DIR_PKG)drivers/
DIR_PKG_TST     := $(DIR_PKG)test/
📁 Derived Download & Extraction Paths
DIR_DL_PKG      := $(DIR_DL)$($(PKG_NAME).DIR)
DIR_EXT_PKG     := $(DIR_EXT)$($(PKG_NAME).DIR)
📁 Output Structure
DIR_INT         := $(DIR_OUT)int/
DIR_LIB         := $(DIR_OUT)lib/
DIR_BIN         := $(DIR_OUT)bin/
DIR_EXT_OUT     := $(DIR_OUT)ext/
DIR_TST         := $(DIR_OUT)test/
📦 Final Artifacts
OUT_BIN         := $(DIR_BIN)$(PKG_NAME)
OUT_LIB         := $(DIR_LIB)$(PKG_NAME).a
OUT_EXT         := $(DIR_EXT_OUT)$(PKG_NAME)/$(TGT_NAME)
OUT_TST         := $(DIR_TST)$(PKG_NAME)
🔧 Build Metadata
$(PKG_NAME).HEADERS :=
$(PKG_NAME).INCLUDES :=
🧠 Notes:
Prefixes like DIR_ for directories, OUT_ for outputs, and PKG_ for metadata help group and distinguish roles.

If you're managing multiple packages, $(PKG_NAME) and $(TGT_NAME) will help generalize targets.

